Benelux governments nationalize part of Fortis bank
The Benelux states help through partial nationalisation the Belgian-Dutch bank Fortis, which ended up in difficulty first in Europe due to the crisis of the American credit market: the three nations will provide €11.2 billion to the financial institution - insurance with interest also in Hungary.
The governments of Belgium, Luxembourg and the Netherlands agreed at the highest level on the weekend, including the President of the European Central Bank and the European Commissioner for Competition.
In the euro area, the first major crisis in the context of the difficulties in which the international financial market has been fighting for more than a year is that of the Fortis bank, and from a certain point of view the decisions taken in this respect may set a precedent.
According to the decision made on Sunday night all three states will hold almost half (49%) of the bank's share in the country.
The bank will almost certainly sell part of its interests, including first of all the assets, especially insurance, of the Dutch ABN Amro acquired a year ago.
Last week the actions of Fortis had begun with a vertical collapse, serious signs of crisis of the institute had then appeared in the second half of the week.
Analysts, however, agree that the bank, with 85,000 employees, is too large to allow it to go bankrupt.
The bank's shares fell by almost 12% on Friday, the lowest point in 14 years.
Since January, the value of shares has decreased by more than two thirds.
Given the current stock prices, the entire capital value of the group is around EUR 14 billion, but according to the bank's management, this value is not real.
The corporate summit imputes the collapse of Fortis actions to the uncertainties of the non-European market due to the acceptance of the US $700 billion plan.
On Monday, the title slowly rose again.
Friday Filip Dierckx was appointed new managing director of the bank.
The financial institution has also sought private buyers but so far no one has come up with a worthy offer.
The Belgian Government had previously assured that investors should not be afraid of losing money.
There was no panic among the bank's clients. The branches were not assaulted.
In Hungary, Fortis has its own subsidiaries and has also purchased leasing companies.
The fox in the hen house
In America, life and health insurers, according to people's medical purchase data, often refuse to enter into an insurance contract.
Privacy experts fear that the data market will become uncontrollable.
"There is a privacy program according to which the use of prescription data of medicines depends in any case on the approval of the person concerned.
This program must be in independent hands, otherwise it is like entrusting the chicken house to the fox "- writes the Washington Post quoting Richard Dick author of the program to follow the prescription of medicines.
Insurance companies shall make the insurance fee and the amount payable in the event of a claim subject to the health status of any customer and shall not take out the insurance if they consider the risk to be too high.
A long time ago, the client had to undergo a medical examination and the contract was only concluded after the examination.
Dick 10 years ago invented a much cheaper procedure: according to the customer's identification code you can easily get information from pharmacies about which medicines he bought in the last year and a half and from this the program shows what diseases he suffers and in what health conditions he is in.
For example, if you regularly buy large amounts of cholesterol reducers, this means that the level of fat in your blood is in practice unconditionally high and is classified in the highest risk category.
On the market there are various versions of the program, some also determine the risk multiplier, so the insurer does not have much left in addition to paper work, even if there are small difficulties.
Among the counter is that some medicines can be used for several purposes, e.g. some compounds can be used against migraine or hot flashes, but they are also effective against depression.
The latter, from an insurance - commercial point of view, is a risk factor, the first two are not.
For the request and data processing have formed separate companies and these, before obtaining the necessary information from pharmacies, ask for the approval of the patient.
The authorities now force them to do so even though they have not yet imposed fines for negligence.
Some firms have also recently developed the results of laboratory tests and linked them to the drug consumption data in order to provide a more accurate picture of patients' health.
More and more companies have access to data and at the same time control of use will be increasingly difficult.
There is a separate privacy law but its validity extends only to health services and insurance.
In front of Congress there is a bill that gives the authorities control powers to the specialized companies in data service.
Richard Dick admits that it is not enough: that is why he has developed a program that connects the forwarding of data with the approval expressed by the person concerned.
Another question is that the person concerned cannot deny approval because otherwise the insurers do not conclude the contract.
So then in the end the chickens are entrusted to the clemency of the fox.
